== Rice ==

Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{300%ml} to the boil with a @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, pop back into the saucepan, cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Preparation ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}.

Halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all).

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Pop the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} into a #bowl{} with the @Cornflour{20%g}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, toss to coat.

Once the oil is hot, add the chicken to the pan and stir-fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Sprinkle on the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%tsp}.

> TIP: Add less if you don't like too much heat.

== Sauce ==

When the chicken is cooked, add the red onions and peppers.

Stir-fry until slightly softened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Lower the heat and stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{64%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Bring to a bubble and cook until the chicken is nicely coated. Remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Mix the coriander and a squeeze of lime juice through the stir-fry.

When the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a fork. Mix in the lime zest. Taste and salt and black pepper if needed.

Chop the remaining lime into wedges.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon your sticky chicken on top. Enjoy!